Upon visually inspecting the cables, an anomalous condition has been detected with the PSU Output Cables:

- Both 'PSU Output Cable (+)' and 'PSU Output Cable (−)' have an observable internal fault: they are short-circuited with each other (short circuit between net_1 and gnd, indicated as 'psu_output_short').

This short circuit constitutes a cable rupture/fault condition and is highly likely to be the source of system issues. All other cables inspected (control and load cables) did not exhibit any observable internal faults or physical concerns based on the step outcomes.

**Recommended Action:**
- Isolate the PSU Output Cables from the system immediately to prevent further damage.
- Correct the short-circuit fault before proceeding with further operations or troubleshooting.
